{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"34dd31a8-34d5-41fc-b136-afc65fb158c7","content":"The equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform is:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `-- --report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `-- --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `-- --crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `-- --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n`--filter` stays on the `dotnet test` side (left of `--`); the SDK translates it for the platform.\n\n**Required NuGet packages** in your test project:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"17.*\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n```\n\nEach `--` flag requires its corresponding extension package to be referenced, otherwise the option is silently ignored or errors out.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"475fb9b2-b0cc-4308-9be5-6c0715da6ce4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`(same) or `--treenode-filter`\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage, or you use a different approach\n- `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` and `--blame-hang-timeout` become `--hangdump` and `--hangdump-timeout`\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, `dotnet test` still works but you pass the platform-specific options after `--` in the command, so the arguments get routed correctly to the test runner instead of being interpreted by the test command itself.\n\nThe filter syntax also changes depending on which compatibility layer you're using—VSTest's `--filter` with its expression syntax works through the compatibility bridge, but Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively uses `--treenode-filter` with a different format like `/*[Tag=Integration]`. Similarly, `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx` (which requires the TrxReport extension package), and code coverage collection shifts from `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` to `--coverage`. I'm realizing I need to clarify how `dotnet test` actually handles Microsoft.Testing.Platform in .NET 8—it acts as a compatibility layer that may or may not map VSTest options directly, so I should verify the exact behavior rather than assume both approaches work interchangeably. With Microsoft.Testing.Platform, I need to include the `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild` package, and platform-specific options like `--report-trx`, `--coverage`, `--crashdump`, and `--hangdump` go after `--` in the command, while the VSTest `--filter` option still works before it.","outputTokens":1671,"requestId":"082D:28F32E:817C267:8FA9BD3:69EABEFE"},"id":"0c83d011-5d0c-4368-b18c-9571875500e0","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:53:45.752Z","parentId":"b4a57099-59a2-4f6a-aa54-7658cd66da2f"}
